      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The user is showing me a BSOD (Blue Screen of Death) with the stop code \"WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR\". They want me to:\n\n1. Investigate this using enterprise root cause analysis\n2. Give it a fixability score using iFix (they probably mean a reliability/fixability assessment)\n3. Tell them how reliable their system is\n4. Whether they can improve PC temperature\n5. Assess if components are okay without stress testing\n6. Use PowerShell and Python tools\n\nLet me think about what I can actually do here:\n\n1. I can run PowerShell commands to check system logs, event viewer, etc.\n2. I can run Python scripts to analyze system information\n3. I can search the web for information about WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR\n\nWHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR is typically related to:\n- Hardware failures (CPU, RAM, motherboard)\n- Overheating issues\n- Power supply problems\n- Overclocking instability\n- Driver issues\n\nLet me start by:\n1. Checking Windows Event Logs for WHEA errors\n2. Checking system temperatures\n3. Checking system information\n4. Doing a web search for more informationI should use PowerShell to gather this information. Let me run some diagnostic commands.",
      "timestamp": 1783146283265
