      "output": "{\n  \"search_id\": \"search_503b40c4593b472281a3539d8372edcb\",\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/how-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error-7c49d78a-2792-96cf-2268-abbe9d9eb29f\",\n      \"title\": \"How to fix WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR - Microsoft Support\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Skip to main content\\n\\n[Microsoft](https://www.microsoft.com)\\n\\nSupport\\n\\n[Support](https://support.microsoft.com/en-us)\\n\\nSupport\\n\\nSearch Search for help\\n\\n* No results Cancel\\n\\nSign in or create an account.\\n\\nHello,\\n\\nSelect a different account.\\n\\nYou have multiple accounts\\n\\nChoose the account you want to sign in with.\\n\\nRelated topics\\n\\n# How to fix WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR\\n\\nApplies To\\n\\nWindows 11 Windows 10\\n\\nWhen a hardware error occurs on a Windows device, it shuts down suddenly and might display a blue screen/stop error with the following error message:\\n\\n**WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR**\\n\\nTo attempt to fix this issue, try the actions from the following list:\\n\\n## Use Windows Update to receive the latest updates and drivers\\n\\nUse Windows Update to receive the latest updates and drivers. For more information on how to use Windows Update to receive the latest updates and drivers, see the following article:\\n\\nAutomatically get recommended drivers and updates for your hardware\\n## Manually update drivers\\n\\nIf the blue screen/stop error gives an indication of which hardware device is causing the issue, the drivers for the hardware device causing the issue can be manually updated. For more information, see the following article:\\n\\nUpdate drivers through Device Manager in Windows\\n\\n**Important:** Microsoft recommends trying to first automatically update drivers using Windows Update. For more information, see the article Automatically get recommended drivers and updates for your hardware .\\n\\n## Use System Restore or Startup Repair\\n\\nUse one of the Windows options to restore or repair Windows. This option is the best option when a recent change was done to the Windows device that could be causing the issue, for example:\\n\\n* Microsoft updates were installed.\\n* An updated driver was installed.\\n* A new app was installed.\\n\\nFor more information, see the following article:\\n\\nRecovery options in Windows\\n\\n## Troubleshoot the blue screen/stop error\\nUse the following article to perform further troubleshooting on the blue screen/stop error:\\n\\nResolving Blue Screen errors in Windows\\n\\n[](https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.microsoft.com%2Fen-us%2Fwindows%2Fhow-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error-7c49d78a-2792-96cf-2268-abbe9d9eb29f \\\"Share on Facebook\\\") [](https://linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=https%3A%2F%2Fsupport.microsoft.com%2Fen-us%2Fwindows%2Fhow-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error-7c49d78a-2792-96cf-2268-abbe9d9eb29f&title=How%20to%20fix%20WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR \\\"Share on LinkedIn\\\") \\n\\nSUBSCRIBE RSS FEEDS\\n\\n### Need more help?\\n\\n### Want more options?\\n\\nDiscover Community\\n\\nExplore subscription benefits, browse training courses, learn how to secure your device, and more.\\n\\n[Microsoft 365 subscription benefits](https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365?ocid=cmmg4dr5b7t)\\n\\nMicrosoft 365 training\\n\\nMicrosoft security\\n\\nAccessibility center\\n\\n## Was this information helpful?\\n\\nYes No\\n\\nThank you!\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://umatechnology.org/whea-uncorrectable-error-troubleshooting-guide-for-2026\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"* **Crash after sleep or wake:** can involve chipset, storage, graphics, network, or power management drivers.\\n* **Crash with no clear pattern:** commonly seen with intermittent RAM faults, aging power supplies, motherboard issues, or marginal overclocks.\\n\\nWindows may create a memory dump file after the crash, and Event Viewer may log entries from sources such as **WHEA-Logger** . These entries can include details like a processor core, cache hierarchy error, PCI Express root port, memory hierarchy error, or bus/interconnect error. Those clues are useful, but they are not always perfectly direct. For example, a WHEA entry mentioning a processor core can be caused by CPU instability, excessive heat, undervolting, motherboard power delivery, outdated firmware, or RAM instability affecting the CPU’s memory controller.\\n\\nThe practical way to interpret this error is to treat it as a stability problem first and a failed-part verdict second.\\n\\n...\\n\\nCheck the drive’s SMART health with the manufacturer’s tool, update SSD firmware, reseat the drive if it is removable, and make sure it has adequate cooling. Back up files immediately if the drive reports media errors, critical warnings, or rapid health decline.\\n\\n### Should I update my BIOS or UEFI to fix WHEA Uncorrectable Error?\\n\\nA BIOS/UEFI update can help if the problem is related to CPU microcode, memory compatibility, PCIe stability, or a newer processor installed on an older motherboard. Use the motherboard or laptop manufacturer’s exact model page, avoid beta firmware unless support recommends it, and do not interrupt the update. After updating, load optimized defaults before reapplying settings such as XMP, EXPO, undervolting, or fan curves.\\n\\n### Is it safe to keep using a PC that gets WHEA Uncorrectable Error?\\n\\nOccasional crashes after a bad driver or unstable tuning may not mean immediate hardware failure, but repeated WHEA errors should not be ignored.\\nContinued use can risk data loss if the cause is storage failure, overheating, or unstable power. Back up your data first, remove overclocks, monitor temperatures, and stop heavy workloads until the system passes stability tests.\\n\\n## Bottom Line\\n\\nThe WHEA Uncorrectable Error is usually a sign that Windows detected a serious hardware or low-level system stability problem, so the safest approach is to troubleshoot methodically: undo recent changes, check temperatures, update BIOS/UEFI and drivers, then test memory, storage, CPU, GPU, and power stability.\\n\\nIf the error continues after clean updates, safe settings, and component diagnostics, treat it as a likely failing part rather than a normal software crash. Back up data, stop overclocking, and consider professional testing or hardware replacement before the issue leads to data loss or an unbootable system.\\n\\n#### Quick Recap\\n\\nBestseller No. 1\\n\\n[Data Recovery software compatible with Windows 11, 10, 8.\\n1, 7 – recover deleted and lost files – rescue deleted images, photos, audios, videos, documents and more](https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09TL7K1TF?tag=umatechnology09-20&linkCode=ogi&th=1&psc=1&keywords=windows+recovery+software \\\"Data Recovery software compatible with Windows 11, 10, 8.1, 7 – recover deleted and lost files – rescue deleted images, photos, audios, videos, documents and more\\\")\\n\\n[Data Recovery software compatible with Windows 11, 10, 8.1, 7 – recover deleted and lost files – rescue deleted images, photos, audios, videos, documents and more](https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09TL7K1TF?tag=umatechnology09-20&linkCode=ogi&th=1&psc=1&keywords=windows+recovery+software \\\"Data Recovery software compatible with Windows 11, 10, 8.1, 7 – recover deleted and lost files – rescue deleted images, photos, audios, videos, documents a\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.techbloat.com/whea-uncorrectable-error-troubleshooting-guide-for-2026.html\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"The timing matters because it can point toward a likely fault domain: crashes under heavy CPU load suggest thermals, voltage, CPU, RAM, or power delivery; crashes during GPU-heavy workloads suggest the graphics card, PCIe slot, GPU driver, or power supply; crashes during file transfers or boot may implicate an SSD, NVMe firmware, storage controller, or filesystem damage.\\n\\n### What “uncorrectable” really implies\\n\\nModern PCs can detect and sometimes recover from minor hardware errors. For example, memory with error correction can fix certain bit errors, and PCIe devices can retry some transactions. An “uncorrectable” WHEA event means the reported fault exceeded what the system could recover from safely. That may be a one-time instability event, but repeated WHEA crashes are a strong signal that something in the hardware, firmware, driver stack, cooling, or power configuration needs attention.\\n* **Single crash after a major change:** often worth investigating recent driver, BIOS, Windows, hardware, or overclocking changes first.\\n* **Repeated crashes under load:** commonly points to heat, voltage instability, RAM settings, GPU issues, or a weak power supply.\\n* **Crashes with disk errors:** may indicate SSD/HDD health problems, NVMe firmware issues, cabling, or storage controller faults.\\n* **Crashes after sleep or resume:** can involve BIOS power management, chipset drivers, GPU drivers, or device firmware.\\n\\nFor troubleshooting, treat WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR as a stability investigation rather than a generic Windows crash. The goal is to identify which layer reported the fault, what changed before the crashes began, and whether the problem follows a pattern. That approach helps separate a bad driver or firmware mismatch from a genuinely failing CPU, RAM module, SSD, graphics card, motherboard, or power supply.\\n\\n## Common Causes: Hardware, Drivers, BIOS, and Overclocking\\nThe WHEA Uncorrectable Error usually appears when Windows receives a severe hardware error report from the processor, chipset, memory controller, PCIe bus, storage controller, or another low-level component. In practice, the cause is not always a completely dead part. It can also be unstable firmware, a bad driver interacting with hardware, aggressive performance settings, overheating, or a power delivery problem that only shows up under load.\\n\\nBecause WHEA errors sit close to the hardware layer, they often happen during demanding tasks: gaming, compiling code, video rendering, running virtual machines, waking from sleep, installing updates, or transferring large files. A system may appear stable on the desktop but crash the moment the CPU boosts, the GPU draws more power, or the SSD controller is stressed. The minidump, Event Viewer entry, or stop code parameters can help narrow the suspect area, but the most common sources fall into a few categories.\\n\\n...\\n\\ncom/amazon-prime-day-deals-live-2026.html) [Embeddable Review: Is It The Best Embedded Analytics Platform in 2025? 02 Embeddable Review: Is It The Best Embedded Analytics Platform in 2025? Articles / Oct 1](https://www.techbloat.com/embeddable-review.html) [10 Best Cases for iPhone 15 and 15 Pro 03 Best Cases for iPhone 15 and 15 Pro Buying Guides / Oct 18](https://www.techbloat.com/best-cases-for-iphone-15-and-15-pro.html) [iPhone 15 Pro Max Magsafe Case 04 Best iPhone 15 Pro Max Magsafe Case Buying Guides / Sep 25](https://www.techbloat.com/best-iphone-15-pro-max-magsafe-case.html) [iPhone 15 Pro Max Case 05 Bеst iPhone 15 Pro Max Cases Buying Guides / Sep 24](https://www.techbloat.com/b%d0%b5st-iphon%d0%b5-15-pro-max-cases.html)\\n\\n## Leave a Reply Cancel reply\\n\\nYour email address will not be published. Required fields are marked \\\\*\\n\\nComment \\\\\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://techlasi.com/pc/whea-uncorrectable-error-troubleshooting-guide\",\n      \"title\": \"WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"# WHEA Uncorrectable Error: Troubleshooting Guide for 2026\\n\\nBy [MK Usmaan](https://techlasi.com/author/mkusman22/ \\\"View all posts by MK Usmaan\\\") / February 12, 2026\\n\\nAre you facing the dreaded blue screen with a WHEA uncorrectable error message? You’re not alone. This frustrating hardware related error has troubled computer users for years, but with advances in diagnostic technology in 2026, we now have better solutions than ever before. This comprehensive guide will walk you through everything you need to know about WHEA errors, from understanding what they are to implementing the most effective fixes using the latest tools and techniques.\\n\\nWHEA Uncorrectable Error\\n\\n## **What is a WHEA Uncorrectable Error?**\\n\\nA WHEA (Windows Hardware Error Architecture) uncorrectable error occurs when Windows detects a serious hardware problem that it cannot recover from automatically.\\nUnlike correctable hardware errors that Windows can resolve on the fly, uncorrectable errors force your system to shut down to prevent potential damage to your hardware or data corruption.\\n\\n### **Windows Hardware Error Architecture**\\n\\nWindows Hardware Error Architecture is a platform level error handling mechanism introduced in [Windows Vista](https://techlasi.com/savvy/windows-vs-linux-vs-macos/) that provides a standardized way for the operating system to handle hardware errors. WHEA improves upon the older Machine Check Architecture by offering enhanced error reporting and more detailed diagnostic information.\\n\\nTable of Contents\\n\\n* What is a WHEA Uncorrectable Error?\\n  \\n    + Windows Hardware Error Architecture\\n    + Common Error Codes Associated with WHEA Errors\\n* Primary Causes of WHEA Uncorrectable Errors\\n  \\n    + Hardware Component Failures\\n    + Overclocking Issues\\n    + Driver and Firmware Problems\\n* Symptoms and Identification of WHEA Uncorrectable Errors\\n+ Blue Screen of Death (BSOD) Appearances\\n    + Event Viewer Diagnostics\\n* Step-by-Step Troubleshooting Guide\\n  \\n    + Immediate Actions to Take\\n    + Advanced Diagnostic Procedures\\n    + Hardware Component Verification\\n* Prevention Strategies for WHEA Errors\\n  \\n    + Proper System Maintenance\\n    + Cooling Solutions and Temperature Management\\n    + Safe Overclocking Practices\\n* Recent Developments in WHEA Error Management\\n  \\n    + Advanced Diagnostic Tools\\n    + AI Assisted Troubleshooting\\n* Conclusion\\n* FAQs\\n  \\n    + Can software cause WHEA uncorrectable errors?\\n    + How can I tell which hardware component is causing my WHEA error?\\n    + Are WHEA errors covered under warranty?\\n    + Can updating BIOS fix WHEA uncorrectable errors?\\n    + Why do WHEA errors sometimes occur only during specific activities like gaming?\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://linustechtips.com/topic/1440210-whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"Whea Uncorrectable Error - Troubleshooting\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2022-06-29\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"com%2Ftopic%2F1440210-whea-uncorrectable-error%2F%3Fdo%3DfindComment%26comment%3D15459738&title=Whea+Uncorrectable+Error \\\"Share on Reddit\\\")\\n\\n* * *\\n\\nMore sharing options...\\n\\n- [](https://linustechtips.com/profile/313534-windows7ge/ \\\"Go to Windows7ge's profile\\\") [](https://linustechtips.com/profile/313534-windows7ge/badges/)\\n* ### **[Windows7ge](https://linustechtips.com/profile/313534-windows7ge/ \\\"Go to Windows7ge's profile\\\")**\\n* Member\\n* Writer of Guides & Tutorials\\n    + [12\\\\.3k](https://linustechtips.com/profile/313534-windows7ge/content/ \\\"12,308 posts\\\")\\n    + [255](https://linustechtips.com/profile/313534-windows7ge/solutions/ \\\"255 solutions\\\")\\n\\n[](https://linustechtips.com/index.php?app=awards&module=awards&controller=awards&do=info&award=4773) [](https://www.boincstats.com/stats/-1/user/detail/73865194514/overview)\\n\\n[](https://linustechtips.com/index.php?app=awards&module=awards&controller=awards&do=info&award=7093)\\n\\n[](https://linustechtips.com/index.php?\\napp=awards&module=awards&controller=awards&do=info&award=7229) [](https://folding.extremeoverclocking.com/user_summary.php?s=&u=1294415)\\n\\n[](https://linustechtips.com/index.php?app=awards&module=awards&controller=awards&do=info&award=7560)\\n\\n[Posted June 29, 2022](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1440210-whea-uncorrectable-error/?do=findComment&comment=15459750)\\n\\n* [](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1440210-whea-uncorrectable-error/ \\\"Share this post\\\")\\n\\nUsually WHEA\\\\_UNCORRECTABLE\\\\_ERROR is associated with a hardware failure. This could be an issue with your PSU, GPU, Motherboard, etc.\\n\\nJust from my experience dealing with this error in the past I'd try a different PSU first but you can try pulling sticks of RAM if you want to test something easier. I wouldn't put my trust in whatever Windows memory check is. Most people use MemTestx86 for memory testing and even then there's no guarantee the memory error will propagate on the first go around.\\nMultiple runs might be required so I'll often just pull a stick at a time and see if the system becomes stable again. Faster. Just as easy.\\n\\n**Guides & Tutorials:**\\n\\n[PROXMOX - Rebuilding ZFS RAID rpool After Disk Failure](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1535985-proxmox-rebuilding-zfs-raid-rpool-after-disk-failure/)\\n\\n[Mass Deploying Customized Windows 10/11 Installs](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1531766-mass-deploying-customized-windows-1011-installs/)\\n\\n[Building a GNU/Linux Based Windows Deployment Server](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1482112-building-a-gnulinux-based-windows-deployment-server/)\\n\\n[GNU/Linux Installer Server: Installation & Configuration](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1445036-gnulinux-installer-server-installation-configuration/)\\n\\n[How to: Use (i)PXE to Install Windows from a Network](https://linustechtips.com/topic/1441143-how-to-use-ipxe-to-install-windows-from-a-network/)\\n\\n[Why Memorize IP's When You Can Self-Host DNS Instead?](https://linustechtips.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.manageengine.com/products/eventlog/kb/resolving-whea-uncorrectable-error-windows-10.html\",\n      \"title\": \"Resolving the WHEA uncorrectable error in Windows 10\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"It can also stem from system file corruption or BIOS misconfigurations. Since this error often indicates a severe issue, addressing it promptly is crucial to prevent further damage or data loss.\\n\\n## Understanding the WHEA uncorrectable error in Windows 10\\n\\nThese errors often indicate underlying hardware issues that require immediate attention. Some common causes of WHEA errors include:\\n\\n* **Faulty hardware:** Defective components, such as the CPU, RAM, motherboard, or storage devices, can be the primary culprits behind these errors. Over time, these components can experience wear and tear, leading to malfunctions or failures.\\n* **Overheating:** Excessive heat can cause hardware components to operate outside their optimal temperature range, leading to instability and potential damage. This is particularly common for components like the CPU and GPU, which generate significant heat during operation.\\n* **Software conflicts:** Incompatible or outdated drivers or software can interfere with hardware operations, causing WHEA errors. This can occur when software is not designed to work correctly with specific hardware configurations or when drivers are not updated to the latest versions.\\n* **Power supply issues:** A faulty power supply can deliver unstable or insufficient power to hardware components, causing them to malfunction or fail. This can be particularly problematic for high-performance systems that require a reliable and consistent power supply.\\n\\n[Ready to secure your SQL server with EventLog Analyzer](https://www.manageengine.com/products/eventlog/download.html?signup=true&utm_source=manageengine&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=log-source-banners&utm_content=logging-guide)\\n\\n## Troubleshooting WHEA uncorrectable errors in Windows 10\\n\\n* There are different ways of troubleshooting the WHEA error.\\nHowever, selecting the right method involves identifying the root cause of the issue. To identify the root cause, we recommend you check your system logs to get more details on the error. To do this, open the **Event Viewer** (search for **Event Viewer** in the **Start** menu).\\n* Navigate to **Windows Logs** > **System** .\\n* Look for entries related to WHEA errors. These entries will provide details about the affected component and error code.\\n\\nThe below methods will help you troubleshoot WHEA errors.\\n\\n* **Identify the faulty component**\\n  \\n    + You can pinpoint the problematic component by examining the Event Viewer data. If the error consistently indicates a specific component, it is probable that this component is the source of the issue.\\n    + For example, if multiple errors are consistently linked to the CPU, it could be experiencing overheating or a hardware defect.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ninjaone.com/blog/how-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error-in-windows-11\",\n      \"title\": \"How to Fix \\\"WHEA_Uncorrectable_Error\\\" in Windows 11 | NinjaOne\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2026-02-24\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Home / Blog / IT Ops / How to Fix the WHEA\\\\_Uncorrectable\\\\_Error in Windows 11\\n\\nIT Ops\\n\\n/\\n\\n* Last updated February 24, 2026\\n\\n/\\n\\n* 6 min read\\n\\n# How to Fix the WHEA\\\\_Uncorrectable\\\\_Error in Windows 11\\n\\n* Picture of Mikhail Blacer Mikhail Blacer\\n\\nby Mikhail Blacer , IT Technical Writer\\n\\nHow to Fix the WHEA Uncorrectable Error in Windows 11 blog banner image\\n\\nTable of contents\\n\\n## Instant Summary\\n\\nSummarize Blog\\n\\nThis NinjaOne blog post offers a comprehensive basic CMD commands list and deep dive into Windows commands with over 70 essential cmd commands for both beginners and advanced users. It explains practical command prompt commands for file management, directory navigation, network troubleshooting, disk operations, and automation with real examples to improve productivity. Whether you’re learning foundational cmd commands or mastering advanced Windows CLI tools, this guide helps you use the Command Prompt more effectively.\\n\\nFree Trial\\n\\n## Key Points\\n* Identify Faulting Hardware: Review WHEA-Logger events in Event Viewer to isolate CPU, memory, PCIe bus, or storage errors.\\n* Update BIOS/UEFI Firmware First: Install vendor-supported firmware updates to fix instability from outdated microcode, voltage control, or PCIe initialization.\\n* Run Targeted Hardware Diagnostics: Stress-test RAM, CPU, and storage using vendor tools or industry-standard diagnostics to confirm whether components fail under load.\\n* Update Chipset, Storage, and Device Drivers: Install the latest supported drivers to correct hardware signaling issues that may trigger repeated WHEA events.\\n* Validate Post-Repair Stability: Clear WHEA logs, apply stress tests, and monitor Event Viewer to ensure the system remains stable without recurring hardware faults.\\n\\nA WHEA (Windows Hardware Error Architecture) Uncorrectable Error (or **whea\\\\_uncorrectable\\\\_error** ) occurs when hardware reports a fault via the WHEA system.\\nIt’s known as a blue screen of death (BSOD) error that comes from failing CPUs, unstable memory, PCIe bus issues, storage faults, or outdated firmware.\\n\\nThis guide delivers a workflow to fix a WHEA Uncorrectable Error. We’ll go through ways on how to identify the hardware source, run targeted diagnostics, update firmware, remove overclocking, and verify system stability.\\n\\n## Steps to fix the WHEA uncorrectable error\\n\\nTo stop the [WHEA uncorrectable error code](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-hardware/drivers/whea/introduction-to-the-windows-hardware-error-architecture) , you will need to perform hardware-focused troubleshooting. Before you go through the steps, you will need to confirm the following requirements:\\n\\n📌 **Prerequisites:**\\n\\n* You will need administrator access on the affected device.\\n* This requires you to enter BIOS or UEFI for firmware and stability changes.\\n* You will need to have tools for memory, CPU, and storage diagnostics.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/answers/questions/3847040/(solved)-experiencing-whea-uncorrectable-error-bso\",\n      \"title\": \"[SOLVED] Experiencing WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR BSOD's on some ...\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2025-06-03\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"I have a custom-built machine that's been crashing lately with some newer games, throwing the WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR code. I checked for dump files but found it's not creating them, and tried to force it to create them; however, no matter the settings I choose, it hangs at 0% when creating a dump file.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/Notebook-Operating-System-and-Recovery/Blue-screen-error-stop-code-WHEA-UNCORRECTABLE-ERROR/td-p/9115716\",\n      \"title\": \"\\n\\tSolved: Blue screen error stop code : WHEA UNCORRECTABLE ERROR - HP Support Community - 9115716\\n\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2024-07-12\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Keep me posted for further assistance\\n\\nPlease mark this post as “ **Accepted Solution** ” if the issue is resolved and if you feel this reply was helpful click “ **Yes** ”.\\n\\n**Nal\\\\_NR-  \\nHP Community Moderator  \\n**\\n\\nView solution in original post\\n\\nTags (1)\\n\\n* Tags:\\n* HP Pavilion Gaming 15-ec1000 Laptop PC (9EK33AV)\\n\\nView All (1)\\n\\nWas this reply helpful? [Yes](https://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/forums/v4/forumtopicpage.externalratingdisplay.ratingenumerationdisplay.link:rating/rating-enum/1/rating-system/medaltesttest/message-uid/9117708?t:ac=board-id/OS/thread-id/662980&t:cp=ratings/contributionpage&ticket=r7TbP0rY_dPL_-1) [No](https://h30434.www3.hp.com/t5/forums/v4/forumtopicpage.externalratingdisplay.ratingenumerationdisplay.link:rating/rating-enum/0/rating-system/medaltesttest/message-uid/9117708?t:ac=board-id/OS/thread-id/662980&t:cp=ratings/contributionpage&ticket=r7TbP0rY_dPL_-1)\\n\\n3 REPLIES 3\\n\\nNal_NR\\n\\nModerator [Nal\\\\_NR](https://h30434.www3.hp.\\ncom/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/4700901)\\n\\n25,525 1,344 1,174 8,387\\n\\nModerator\\n\\n‎07-09-2024 07:46 AM\\n\\nHP Recommended\\n\\n* Mark as New\\n* Bookmark\\n* Subscribe\\n* \\n* Permalink\\n* Print\\n* \\n* Flag Post\\n\\nHi @AS773 ,\\n\\nWelcome to the HP Support Community.\\n\\nI'd be happy to help you!\\n\\nThe \\\"WHEA UNCORRECTABLE ERROR\\\" is typically associated with hardware issues. Since you've already tried updating the BIOS, formatting the C drive, and checking for bad sectors, there are a few other steps you can take to troubleshoot and potentially resolve the issue:\\n\\n**Check for Driver Issues** :\\n\\n* Ensure all your device drivers are up to date, especially for critical components like your GPU, CPU, and chipset.\\n\\n**Run Windows Memory Diagnostic** :\\n\\n* Press Win + R, type mdsched.exe, and press Enter.\\n* Choose \\\"Restart now and check for problems.\\\"\\n\\n**Check Event Viewer Logs** :\\n\\n* Press Win + X and select Event Viewer.\\n* Navigate to Windows Logs > System and look for critical errors around the time of the BSOD.\\n**Stress Test Your Hardware** :\\n\\n* Use tools like Prime95 to stress test your CPU and MemTest86 for RAM.\\n\\n**Update Firmware/Drivers** :\\n\\n* Visit the HP support website and ensure all firmware and drivers for your specific model (HP Pavilion Gaming 15-Ec1000) are up to date.\\n\\n**Disable Overclocking** :\\n\\n* If you have any overclocking settings enabled in the BIOS or through software, disable them and see if the issue persists.\\n\\n**Check for Overheating** :\\n\\n* Use software like HWMonitor to check the temperatures of your CPU and GPU to ensure they are not overheating.\\n\\n**Reseat Hardware Components** :\\n\\n* If comfortable, try reseating your RAM, SSD/HDD, and other removable components to ensure they are properly connected.\\n\\n**Run System File Checker (SFC) and DISM** :\\n\\n* Open Command Prompt as an administrator.\\n* Run sfc /scannow and wait for it to complete.\\n* Then run DISM /Online /Cleanup-Image /RestoreHealth.\\n\\n**Check PSU and Battery** :\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/experience/performance-optimization/how-to-fix-whea-uncorrectable-error\",\n      \"title\": \"How to fix WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"How to fix WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR\\nHow to fix WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR · Use Windows Update to receive the latest updates and drivers · Manually update drivers · Use System Restore or Startup Repair.\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"warnings\": null,\n  \"usage\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"sku_search\",\n      \"count\": 1\n    }\n  ],\n  \"session_id\": \"ses_0d4353d89ffexQGwsnzdBDw5HE\"\n}",
