      "text": "Now I have a good picture. Let me run Python-based diagnostics for temperature and hardware health checks. Let me also check for any overclocking settings.\n\nKey findings:\n1. HP OMEN Laptop 15-ce0xx with i5-7300HQ, GTX 1050, 16GB mixed RAM\n2. Crash dump is enabled (type 7 = Automatic memory dump) but no minidump files found - this means crashes ARE happening but dump files might be getting cleaned up3. TPM-WMI errors related to secure boot updates - not directly related but concerning\n4. XTU3SERVICE timeout - Intel XTU service failing to start (this is Intel Extreme Tuning Utility - could indicate overclocking software issues)\n5. Battery at 100% charged, design voltage 13074mV\n\nLet me run more diagnostics with Python tools to check temperatures and hardware health.",
